-- ── Cricket Health ──────────────────────────────────────────────
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Cricket Health was a technology-enabled kidney care company that provided value-based care management for patients with chronic kidney disease (CKD) and end-stage renal disease (ESRD). In August 2022, Cricket Health completed a three-way merger with InterWell Health and Fresenius Health Partners, and the combined organization now operates under the InterWell Health brand. As of 2026, Cricket Health no longer exists as a standalone, independently branded company; its technology and patient engagement platform were folded into InterWell Health's value-based kidney care operations.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Not applicable as a standalone product; historically a value-based care company contracting with health plans and providers rather than a subscription software vendor$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Not applicable (discontinued as a standalone brand; not consumer or self-serve priced)$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2014, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$Not applicable as a standalone entity since 2022 (folded into InterWell Health, which reports serving hundreds of thousands of kidney disease patients nationally)$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$Formerly San Francisco, California, United States (now part of InterWell Health, headquartered in Waltham, Massachusetts)$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Cricket Health: History, InterWell Health Merger and Status$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Cricket Health merged into InterWell Health in 2022. Learn its history, care model, and current status as of 2026.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Cricket Health was a venture-backed, technology-enabled kidney care company founded in 2014 by former LinkedIn executive Arvind Rajan and former Aberdare Ventures general partner Vince Kim, and it publicly launched its value-based chronic kidney disease (CKD) care model in 2016. The company was headquartered in San Francisco, California, and built a technology and patient engagement platform designed to identify at-risk kidney disease patients earlier, support them through education and multidisciplinary care teams, and help them make more informed treatment decisions, including planned rather than emergency starts to dialysis and increased use of home dialysis and kidney transplant options. Cricket Health's business model was built around value-based care contracts with health plans and provider groups, meaning it was paid based on improving patient outcomes and reducing the total cost of care for chronic kidney disease and end-stage renal disease populations, rather than selling software licenses or consumer subscriptions directly. The company raised early venture funding, including a 2.5 million dollar seed round led by First Round Capital, BoxGroup, Seven Peaks Ventures, Nexus Venture Partners, and NFX Guild, and later funding rounds including roughly 24 million dollars raised by 2018 to expand its footprint in the kidney care space. The most important fact for anyone researching Cricket Health in 2026 is that it no longer exists as an independent, separately branded company. In August 2022, Cricket Health completed a three-way merger with InterWell Health and Fresenius Health Partners, a division of Fresenius Medical Care North America, in a transaction reported to be valued at approximately 2.4 billion dollars. The combined organization retained the InterWell Health name rather than the Cricket Health name, and Cricket Health's technology-enabled care model and patient engagement platform were integrated into InterWell Health's broader value-based kidney care operations. InterWell Health is now headquartered at 920 Winter Street, Waltham, Massachusetts, and operates as one of the largest value-based kidney care providers in the United States, working with a large network of nephrologists, historically cited at more than 1,600, and aiming to serve several hundred thousand patients with chronic kidney disease and end-stage renal disease. Because Cricket Health has been absorbed into InterWell Health, there is no longer a standalone Cricket Health product, pricing page, or company website functioning independently; searches for Cricket Health in 2026 should be understood as referring to a discontinued brand whose capabilities live on inside InterWell Health. Any directory listing, comparison, or review referencing Cricket Health as an active, separately operating company would be inaccurate as of 2026, and this entry is written to reflect that historical and current status honestly rather than describing Cricket Health as if it were still a currently operating standalone product. For readers actually looking for the active kidney care organization that resulted from this merger, InterWell Health is the correct current entity to research, as it now carries forward Cricket Health's technology-enabled care approach alongside Fresenius Health Partners' value-based contracting expertise and InterWell Health's nephrology network.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '6f5f09e5-d368-4bc6-b9cd-16e74d0398f9';

